          "text": "<path>/home/matej/pers/remembeer/CLAUDE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # CLAUDE.md\n2: \n3: This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n4: \n5: ## Project Overview\n6: \n7: Remembeer is a Flutter mobile app (iOS & Android) for tracking drinks with social features: sessions, leaderboards, badges, and friends. Backend is Firebase (Auth, Firestore, Storage, Cloud Functions, Messaging). Firebase region: europe-west4.\n8: \n9: ## Common Commands\n10: \n11: ```bash\n12: # Install dependencies\n13: flutter pub get\n14: \n15: # Run code generation (freezed, json_serializable, go_router_builder, interface_generator)\n16: dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs\n17: \n18: # Format\n19: dart format .\n20: \n21: # Lint (strict — CI uses --fatal-warnings)\n22: flutter analyze --fatal-warnings\n23: ```\n24: \n25: **CI checks that generated files (`*.g.dart`, `*.freezed.dart`) are committed and up-to-date.** Always run build_runner after changing models or routes and commit the generated output.\n26: \n27: ## Architecture\n28: \n29: ### Layered Feature Structure\n30: \n31: Each feature lives in `lib/<feature>/` with up to four layers:\n32: \n33: | Layer | Directory | Role |\n34: |---|---|---|\n35: | **Model** | `model/` | Immutable data classes via freezed. Entities extend `Entity` (has `userId`, timestamps, soft-delete `deletedAt`). DTOs extend `ValueObject`. |\n36: | **Controller** | `controller/` | Firestore CRUD. Extend `CrudController<T extends Entity, U extends ValueObject>`. No business logic. |\n37: | **Service** | `service/` | Business logic. Use RxDart (`BehaviorSubject`, `combineLatest`, `switchMap`) for reactive state. |\n38: | **Page/Widget** | `page/`, `widget/` | UI. Pages are full screens; widgets are reusable components. |\n39: \n40: ### Dependency Injection\n41: \n42: GetIt via `lib/ioc/ioc_container.dart`. All singletons registered in `IoCContainer.initialize()` in order: basic services, then controllers, then services. Access with `get<T>()`.\n43: \n44: ### Routing\n45: \n46: go_router with go_router_builder for type-safe routes. Route definitions in `lib/routes.dart`, generated code in `routes.g.dart`. NavbarShellRoute provides 5 bottom tabs: Profile, Leaderboards, Drink (home), Activity, Settings.\n47: \n48: ### Code Generation\n49: \n50: Four generators configured in `build.yaml`:\n51: - **freezed**: Immutable data classes (`*.freezed.dart`)\n52: - **json_serializable**: JSON serialization with `explicit_to_json: true` (`*.g.dart`)\n53: - **go_router_builder**: Type-safe routes (`routes.g.dart`)\n54: - **interface_generator**: Custom generator in `packages/interface_generator/` — generates `*Fields` abstract classes from `*Core` classes\n55: \n56: ### Key Patterns\n57: \n58: - **Soft deletes**: Entities use `deletedAt` field, never hard-deleted from Firestore\n59: - **Server timestamps**: `withServerCreateTimestamps()`, `withServerUpdateTimestamp()`, `withServerDeleteTimestamps()` extension methods on JSON maps\n60: - **Ownership**: All entities have a `userId` field; Firestore rules enforce ownership-based access\n61: - **Global entities**: Some entities (e.g., seed drink types) use a special `globalUserId` and cannot be modified from the app\n62: \n63: ### Cloud Functions\n64: \n65: Python 3.13 functions in `functions/main.py` — push notification triggers for friend requests and session invites.\n66: \n67: ## UI Patterns\n68: \n69: ### Page Structure\n70: \n71: Every page wraps its content in `PageTemplate` (Scaffold + AppBar + SafeArea + padding). Settings-style pages use `SettingsPageTemplate` which adds a hint box and optional save FAB.\n72: \n73: Typical page skeleton:\n74: \n75: ```dart\n76: class SomePage extends StatelessWidget {\n77:   SomePage({super.key});\n78: \n79:   final _someService = get<SomeService>();\n80: \n81:   @override\n82:   Widget build(BuildContext context) {\n83:     return PageTemplate(\n84:       title: const Text('Title'),\n85:       child: AsyncBuilder<SomeModel>(\n86:         stream: _someService.someStream,\n87:         builder: (context, data) {\n88:           return /* UI using data */;\n89:         },\n90:       ),\n91:     );\n92:   }\n93: }\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ### AsyncBuilder\n97: \n98: `AsyncBuilder<T>` is the primary way to connect reactive data to UI. It accepts either a `stream` or a `future` (exactly one), handles loading/error states by default, and calls `builder` when data is available. Use it instead of raw `StreamBuilder`/`FutureBuilder`. Pages often nest multiple AsyncBuilders for independent data sources.\n99: \n100: ### Service Access in Pages\n101: \n102: Pages obtain services as final fields via `get<T>()` (not in `build()`). Services expose `Stream`s for reactive data and `Future`s for one-shot operations. Pages hold no local state beyond what services provide — the service layer owns all business state via RxDart streams.\n103: \n104: ### Forms\n105: \n106: Use `LoadingForm` for any form with async submission. It provides:\n107: - `buildTextField()`, `buildPasswordField()`, `buildSubmitButton()`, `buildErrorMessage()` — consistent styled inputs\n108: - `runAction()` — wraps async calls with loading spinner and error handling\n109: - `validate()` — form validation\n110: - Optional `errorMapper` for translating exceptions to user-facing messages\n111: \n112: ### Destructive Actions\n113: \n114: Use `showConfirmationDialog()` from `lib/common/action/confirmation_dialog.dart` for any destructive action. Set `isDestructive: true` to style the button with error color.\n115: \n116: ### Notifications\n117: \n118: Use `showSuccessNotification()` or `showNotification()` from `lib/common/action/notifications.dart` for toast feedback (toastification package, 4s auto-close).\n119: \n120: ### Navigation\n121: \n122: - **Tab routes**: Use typed go_router routes (e.g., `const FriendRequestsRoute().go(context)`)\n123: - **Sub-pages/modals**: Use `Navigator.of(context).push(MaterialPageRoute(...))` for detail/edit pages not in the tab structure\n124: - **After deletion**: `Navigator.of(context).popUntil((route) => route.isFirst)` to return to root\n125: \n126: ### Styling Conventions\n127: \n128: - Colors always via `Theme.of(context).colorScheme.*` — never hardcoded (except notifications, which have a TODO for this)\n129: - Spacing via `Gap` widget (from gap package), not manual SizedBox\n130: - Cards typically use `Card(child: ListTile(...))` pattern\n131: - Empty states: centered Column with large muted icon + title + subtitle text\n132: - Button types: `FilledButton` for primary actions, `OutlinedButton`/`TextButton` for secondary, `ElevatedButton.icon` for profile actions\n133: \n134: ## Lint Rules\n135: \n136: Extremely strict analysis_options.yaml with ~120 rules. Notable enforced patterns:\n137: - `always_use_package_imports` (no relative imports)\n138: - `prefer_single_quotes`\n139: - `prefer_final_locals` and `prefer_final_in_for_each`\n140: - `avoid_print` (no print statements)\n141: - `prefer_const_constructors` and `prefer_const_literals_to_create_immutables`\n142: - `avoid_dynamic_calls` with strict-casts, strict-inference, strict-raw-types\n143: - `flutter_style_todos` (TODOs must be `// TODO(username): message`)\n144: - `sort_pub_dependencies`\n\n(End of file - total 144 lines)\n</content>",
